race.comment: LAVISH CHARM (1) has won both starts this preparation easily from the front and the 3kg claim takes care of the weight rise. He's promising and fitter again should have these well covered. BLITZEM BABE (5) found the company a bit rich last time but has been threatening a win the three prior. Faithful replaces the 3kg apprentice and she can make the finish. CALL TIME (6) comes out of the same race and didn't get warm after settling last from the 11 gate. The two runs prior read well enough and he maps well today with a 3kg claimer engaged. MARGOT'S BULLSEYE (7) resumes and can use the inside barrier. Usually needs a run but he has shown enough to keep onside. THATSTHEWAYILIKEIT (3) is sure to show more second-up.
